### Approaches Used in Treatment (CBT, Therapy Options)

Several effective therapy options are available for social anxiety treatment. These evidence-based approaches help teens understand and change the patterns that fuel their anxiety. The goal is to reduce the symptoms of social anxiety disorder and build lasting confidence.

Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT) is the most commonly used approach. This type of behavioral therapy helps teens identify the negative thought patterns that drive their fear and replace them with healthier, more realistic ones. Another powerful method is exposure therapy, which involves gradually and safely facing feared social situations until they become less intimidating. In some cases, medication may be used alongside therapy. Common approaches include:

- Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT)
- Exposure Therapy
- Social skills training
- Group therapy
- Medication, such as SSRIs, when appropriate

These treatments provide teens with practical tools to manage their anxiety. By learning to challenge their fears and practice new behaviors, they can break free from the cycle of social anxiety.

